Khartoum Hospital officials said 10 people were being treated for injuries, including four in critical condition.
Early Friday, Sudanese demonstrators stormed the empty U.S. Embassy compound in Khartoum and pulled down the American flag to protest the attack.
American diplomats were pulled out of Khartoum in 1996.
El-Bashir said that the factory _ the El-Shifa Pharmaceutical Industries Co. in the North Khartoum neighborhood _ was hit by six Tomahawk missiles.
